    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="408"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <head>408. Paper Prepared by the Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian and
                    Pacific Affairs (<persName>Bundy</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d408fn1">Source: National Archives and Records Administration,
                            <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Bundy Files: Lot 85 D 240, Top
                        Secret WPB Chron., Nov.–Dec. 1967. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-11-20">November 20, 1967</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">JCS Recommendations, with <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>
                        positions, and recommended State position:</hi>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Remove restrictions on all militarily significant targets in <gloss
                                target="#t_NVN1">NVN</gloss>. <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—No</item>
                                <item>State—No</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Mine <gloss target="#t_NVN1">NVN</gloss> deep water ports. <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—No</item>
                                <item>State—No</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Mine inland waterways and estuaries in <gloss target="#t_NVN1"
                                >NVN</gloss> north of 20oN. <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—Yes, with prohibition
                                    against mining within 5 miles of any deep water ports and within
                                    25 miles of Chinese border.</item>
                                <item>State—Yes</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Extend naval surface operations (Sea Dragon).<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d408fn2">Operations along the North Vietnamese coast up to
                                the 20th parallel.</note>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—Yes</item>
                                <item>State—Yes, but with careful restrictions.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Use <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_SAM1">SAM</gloss>s (TALOS)<note n="3" xml:id="d408fn3"
                                >A specific type of surface-to-air missile.</note> from ships
                            against combat aircraft. <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—Yes</item>
                                <item>State—No</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>
                            <p>Increase air interdiction in Laos and along <gloss target="#t_NVN1"
                                    >NVN</gloss> borders. <list>
                                    <item>
                                        <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—No (since present
                                        arrangements with RLG are adequate)</item>
                                    <item>State—No</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SWH1">Sullivan</persName>—believes more should
                                be done, especially during the next two months, but under present
                                arrangements with RLG. Notes that <persName corresp="#p_SP1"
                                    >Souvanna</persName> would favor such an increase.</p>
                        </item>
                        <label>7.</label>
                        <item>
                            <p>Eliminate operational restrictions on <gloss target="#t_B521"
                                    >B–52</gloss>s with regard to Laos. <list>
                                    <item>
                                        <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—Yes</item>
                                    <item>State—check with <persName corresp="#p_SWH1"
                                            >Sullivan</persName>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SWH1">Sullivan</persName>—Yes on night-time
                                overflights, selected daylight bombing subject to clearance, and
                                limited penetrations subject to clearance; No on blanket bombing
                                authority or “indiscriminate” day-time overflights.</p>
                        </item>
                        <pb facs="1090" n="1050" xml:id="pg_1050"/>
                        <label>8.</label>
                        <item>
                            <p>Expand operations in Laos (Prairie Fire).<note n="4" xml:id="d408fn4"
                                    >Guerrilla and reconnaissance operations in the part of Laos
                                    closest to the border with Vietnam.</note>
                                <list>
                                    <item>
                                        <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—Yes “Examine
                                        sympathetically,” have <gloss target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss>
                                        and <persName corresp="#p_SWH1">Sullivan</persName>
                                        coordinate on a selective basis.</item>
                                    <item>
                                        <p>State—Have <gloss target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> and
                                                <persName corresp="#p_SWH1">Sullivan</persName> work
                                            out, subject to final approval here.</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <persName corresp="#p_SWH1">Sullivan</persName>—prepared
                                            to work with <gloss target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss>, but
                                            wishes to retain final Washington approval; indicates
                                            clearly negative attitude on battalion- or company-size
                                            operations. No to the Gung-Ho warriors; and keep
                                            Washington involved as restraint.</p>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                        </item>
                        <label>9.</label>
                        <item>Expand operations in Cambodia (Daniel Boone).<note n="5"
                                xml:id="d408fn5">Clandestine ground reconnaissance into an area in
                                Cambodia within 20 kilometers of the South Vietnamese border.</note>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—No.</item>
                                <item>State—No, at least for the present, but could be subject to
                                    review depending on Sihanouk behavior.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>10.</label>
                        <item>Expand and reorient <gloss target="#t_NVN1">NVN</gloss> covert
                            programs (Footboy).<note n="6" xml:id="d408fn6">The overall program of
                                clandestine operations against North Vietnam; formerly known as
                                Operations Plan 34-Alpha.</note>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>—Yes (as means of getting
                                    more intelligence)</item>
                                <item>State—Yes in principle, but need more information to be sure
                                    proposals do not raise political problems.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
